<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>We&nbsp;would like to thank you for your posts.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>There are many viewpoints that can be considered with Live Quests and Events that can be, and are expressed here in this thread.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Before&nbsp;we continue,&nbsp;we urge posters here to read our EverQuest Legends: Dynamic Events FAQ available at: <namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><A href="http://legends.everquest.station.sony.com/devview.jsp?o=61443" target=_blank>http://legends.everquest.station.sony.com/devview.jsp?o=61443</A> .<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Please bear in mind, Dynamic Events will continue to have Dynamic Rewards as well.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Whether there becomes an opportunity for your raiding party to loot droppable items at a Quest, or whether the GM/Actor rewards characters in a random or deliberate fashion, there will be a variety of results.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT size=2>To limit all Quest rewards to GM-only distribution would be to eliminate the possibility that your character could find something useful to it during a Live Quest.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Having said this, it would also be limiting (and possibly not entertaining) to only have items drop dynamically or deliberately from NPC's exclusively.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>In point of fact, these are not the only options for loot distribution or acquisition.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT size=2>Loot given at a Dynamic Quest should not be viewed as a "right" or "guarantee", but a benefit.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>On occasion, your character may not benefit from a loot reward, and for this to occur is natural and possible.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>The GM/Actor works within certain limitations when offering any possible reward, we do not deliberately remove or include any class or race unless it is called for in a story-context.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Furthermore, if a GM/Actor is classed as a Warrior, you might not expect a reward of say a spell scroll (though sometimes this may actually occur). It may be frustrating that a player at an event may not handle a distribution of loot to your satisfaction.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Each Live Quest brings new challenges to the players concerned, and choosing Looters, and Leaders is part of how a Dynamic Quest can work.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>It can be encouraged before a Quest begins, that the players make an agreement on looting and stick to it.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Whether your choice is NGB (need before greed), or FFA (free for all), or any other way, this can be arranged by the players pre-Quest and is encouraged.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>In the end, if your character feels dissatisfied with the outcome of loot arrangements, do not despair.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Norrath is a dynamic world, and you will most certainly get another chance!<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal none? mso-layout-grid-align: 0pt; 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN New?? ?Courier FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT size=2>Players who have attended recent quests can speak on their own experiences here, but we would like you to know that your concerns are being heard on a team-level.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>We do hope you will enjoy the Live Quest content only available on Stormhammer, and look forward to providing many more chances for you and your character to explore Stormhammer and your Legends service.</FONT></SPAN></P>
